245
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:22,340
Nami, are you feeling sick?

246
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:27,300
Nami, do you want one piece
of meat? Just one piece, though.

247
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,900
Nami-san, you're thinking
about Vivi-chan, right?

248
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:36,310
I understand how you're feeling...
but thinking doesn't get you anywhere.

249
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:39,750
Yeah, I know... you two were really close...

250
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:42,270
But hey... chin up.

251
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:48,220
I...

252
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:55,580
For Vivi's sake... I'm willing to give up...

253
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,080
...on the 1 billion berries...

254
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:59,870
--Of course you should!
--So it was about money?!

255
00:15:00,230 --> 00:15:01,740
Ah! Usopp fell!

256
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:04,010
Nami! Don't act misleading!

257
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:06,220
What?! What're you guys worked up about?

258
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:08,640
If it's about Vivi, it's no use
worrying about it, right?

259
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,300
Hey! Usopp fell!

260
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,800
Leave him be.

261
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:13,460
It was your fault!

262
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,940
Karoo! Where are you, Karoo?!

263
00:15:18,310 --> 00:15:19,980
It's no use, Igaram.

264
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:23,600
Why? We should at least let them
know their current situation.

265
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:27,390
Since I had the Duck Squadron
take them, even Karoo can't catch up.

266
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:28,750
And it won't change anything...

267
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:30,030
What won't change?

268
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:34,240
They'll be happy when they know it.
That's all. Nothing will change.

269
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:37,130
--But...!
--They'll be fine!

270
00:15:37,130 --> 00:15:41,000
Now, leave! I'm going to bed!
You have to get up early, right?

271
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:45,710
Ah... yes. That's right. We have to let
the entire country hear your voice.

272
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:49,590
I know. Come here, Karoo.
Let's sleep together.

273
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:58,000
--Hmm...
--Igaram-san.

274
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,320
Something's bothering me...

275
00:15:59,320 --> 00:15:59,890
What is it?

276
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:04,640
She's too calm... Hmm...

277
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:07,610
Strange... There's something strange...

278
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:17,820
It's quiet, isn't it, Karoo?

279
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:22,040
We haven't had a quiet night
like this for a long time...

280
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:26,200
The cook who fights with
the fridge robber is gone...

281
00:16:26,790 --> 00:16:29,580
The swordsman who trains
every night is also gone...

282
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:32,780
The navigator who throws her
pillow half asleep is gone, too...

283
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,930
They're all gone...

284
00:16:39,620 --> 00:16:42,020
Transponder snail
communication? From who?

285
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:44,060
From someone named Bon-chan.

286
00:16:44,060 --> 00:16:45,550
Bon-chan? Who's that?

287
00:16:45,550 --> 00:16:47,080
No one knows him.

288
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,900
But he insists he's your friend, so...

289
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:50,980
Our friend?

290
00:16:52,470 --> 00:16:55,000
Hello? Hi there!

291
00:16:56,180 --> 00:16:59,410
It's me! Me! Uhm...

292
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:03,240
What?! Shut up!

293
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:07,120
Hey, it's you, huh?
What do you want from us?

294
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:10,090
Oh? That voice must be Straw Hat, right?

295
00:17:10,370 --> 00:17:13,640
You're strong! I was so surprised!

296
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:16,840
Oh, yeah... Don't call me Mr. 2.

297
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:19,900
If this signal is caught by
the Navy, I'll be in trouble.

298
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,770
You just said it yourself!

299
00:17:21,770 --> 00:17:23,200
Just tell us what you want!

300
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:26,700
Oh, yeah... I took your ship.

301
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:27,600
That's not funny!

302
00:17:27,970 --> 00:17:30,590
You son of a bitch! This isn't a
joking matter! Where're you now?!

303
00:17:30,590 --> 00:17:32,700
On your ship.

304
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:34,240
Of all others, he...

305
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:37,570
No, no...! Gee...

306
00:17:37,970 --> 00:17:41,850
We're friends, right?

307
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:50,020
He's at the upper reaches
of the Sandora River...

308
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:52,190
Can we trust him?

309
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:54,430
We became friends one time, but...

310
00:17:54,430 --> 00:17:56,990
In your case, you may be able to make
friends with him again, which is scary...

311
00:17:56,990 --> 00:17:58,800
But we have no choice but to go...

312
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,970
He's right. He has our ship.

313
00:18:00,970 --> 00:18:04,270
If he tries to trick us,
then we'll just beat him up.

314
00:18:04,270 --> 00:18:06,200
Now that it's decided, let's get ready quickly.

315
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:09,240
Okay! Let's hurry. If we don't
get there quickly, our ship will...

316
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:10,480
Say, everyone...

317
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:16,630
Say... everyone...

318
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:22,280
What... should I do...?

319
00:18:24,740 --> 00:18:28,400
Listen well, Vivi. We'll give you 12 hours.

320
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:32,710
"Current Location: Alubarna"
"Nanohana" "Sandora River"

321
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:31,340
Once we take our ship
back on the Sandora River,

322
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:36,160
we'll draw the ship near the eastern harbor
just once at exactly noon tomorrow.

323
00:18:32,710 --> 00:18:37,590
"Eastern Harbor"

324
00:18:36,130 --> 00:18:37,590
We probably won't be able to anchor.

325
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:41,310
If you want to continue traveling with us,

326
00:18:41,310 --> 00:18:43,630
that moment is the only
chance to come aboard.

327
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:48,480
If that happens, we'll welcome you...
though you'll become a pirate.

328
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:52,750
Since you're a princess of a country,
this is the best we can do to invite you.

329
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:55,310
Come, Vivi! Definitely come! Come now!

330
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:56,940
--Stop it, Luffy.
--Let's go.

331
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,630
Why?! Don't you want her to come?

332
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:02,910
That's not the point!
It's something Vivi has to decide!

333
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:10,200
Noon tomorrow...

334
00:19:10,710 --> 00:19:13,940
If it's the eastern harbor, it'll take
four hours to get there on Karoo...

335
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:16,540
If I leave here at 8, I'll make it on time...

336
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:21,100
I've never thought of becoming a pirate.

337
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:27,850
If I miss this chance, I'll never have
such a choice for the rest of my life...

338
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:32,760
I've never thought that being
a princess was uninteresting,

339
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:36,360
and the country is still at a critical point,
though the rebellion is over...

340
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:44,010
If I go, you'll go too, right?

341
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:48,040
Say... Karoo...

342
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:52,860
What... would you like to do?

343
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:57,950
I've been waiting, you guys!

344
00:19:57,950 --> 00:20:00,090
Long time no see!

345
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:01,360
We're here!

346
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:04,170
Okay, unload! Thanks, you guys!

347
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:06,570
We have to say goodbye to you here.

348
00:20:06,570 --> 00:20:07,720
Have a safe trip back!

349
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:11,020
Say hello to the King, the old
tube-hair guy and the others!

350
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:12,730
Take care!

351
00:20:12,730 --> 00:20:18,400
I'll see you... definitely
see you again someday!

352
00:20:19,590 --> 00:20:22,110
Hm? Wait a sec!

353
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:24,490
--What?!
--Don't "what" me!

354
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:28,200
That's not how you should
treat your friend, is it?!

355
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:32,040
What do you mean "friend"?
We were enemies. You lied to us!

356
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:35,900
I didn't lie! I didn't know it, either!

357
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:38,750
But you see... who cares about it anymore?

358
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:42,990
Baroque Works fell. We're no longer enemi...

359
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:44,630
--Hey, move over...
--Oh, sorry.

360
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:49,530
Even if we're not enemies,
why are you on our ship?!

361
00:20:49,530 --> 00:20:51,600
--You stupid head!
--What'd you say?!

362
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:54,560
Listen! If I wasn't on this ship now,

363
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:57,060
what do you think would've happened to it?!

364
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:59,400
It might've been taken by the Navy.

365
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,780
--What?!
--It's not "might've"!
It definitely would've happened!

366
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:04,900
Do you know what's going on
around this island right now?!

367
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:07,740
It's completely blocked by
the Navy ships! It's blocked!

368
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:12,280
What?! Then you protected
the Going Merry from the Navy?!

369
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:13,450
--Why?!
--How come?!

370
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,000
Because we're friends!

371
00:21:23,970 --> 00:21:25,040
Do we still have stuff to load?

372
00:21:25,040 --> 00:21:26,510
Nope. This is the last one.

373
00:21:26,870 --> 00:21:28,680
In other words, Mr. 2...

374
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:32,780
You guys couldn't get off of the
island due to the Navy's coast siege,

375
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:35,030
so you wanted to find allies...
Isn't that right?

376
00:21:35,030 --> 00:21:36,230
Bon-chan!

377
00:21:36,690 --> 00:21:40,030
That's right... In a time like this...
Because it's a time like this...

378
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:42,090
Gather! In the name of friendship!

379
00:21:42,090 --> 00:21:44,690
Let's unite our strength and fight together!

380
00:21:44,930 --> 00:21:48,250
Yeah!

381
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:49,160
Geez...

382
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:51,530
Yeah!

383
00:21:51,530 --> 00:21:52,830
So, thanks in advance!

384
00:21:52,830 --> 00:21:54,370
You were there?!

385
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,330
Miss Hina! Miss Hina!

386
00:21:57,330 --> 00:22:00,360
We found it! We found the Straw Hats' ship!

387
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,840
Near the upper reaches of the Sandora River!

388
00:22:03,910 --> 00:22:05,550
Prepare to fight.

389
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:27,240
Which direction should I run towards
to see a more wonderful tomorrow?

390
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:33,160
I took the helm and opened the
miraculous map that I stored in my heart

391
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:39,420
I aimed for the sky and sought out
my dreams, though at times I got lost

392
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:44,840
It wasn't a dream; when I met you,
I discovered the wonderful person in me

393
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:51,090
With just a bit of courage,
I gained something grand

394
00:22:51,090 --> 00:22:56,520
Now's the time for my "wish"
to become my "pledge"

395
00:22:57,270 --> 00:23:00,320
Shining ray! Find your brand new way

396
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:04,020
Let's sketch out the tale of the future

397
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:09,280
I'll put all my feelings
in a brand new wind now

398
00:23:09,280 --> 00:23:12,400
Shining ray! Find your brand new way

399
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:15,280
A never-ending journey to be together

400
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:19,930
I'll chase after you
wherever you go, Shining ray

401
00:23:25,830 --> 00:23:27,210
Vivi will come, right?

402
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:29,500
Adventures are fun.
There's no way she won't come.

403
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:32,560
Give up, Luffy. Her case
is different from ours.

404
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,800
Hey, this is bad! The Navy
is following us again!

405
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:37,340
There's no way she won't come!
She'll be a pirate with us!

406
00:23:37,340 --> 00:23:41,000
Father... Igaram... I have something
important to talk with you about.

407
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,300
On the next episode of One Piece!

408
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,900
"It All Started on That Day!
Vivi Tells the Story of Her Adventure!"

409
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:47,590
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
